answer.en:
### Express with fs and path

Use path.join() to safely resolve file paths and fs.readFile() to serve content asynchronously. Always handle errors gracefully to prevent server crashes.

```typescript
import express from 'express';
import fs from 'fs/promises';
import path from 'path';

const app = express();

app.get('/file/:name', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const filePath = path.join(process.cwd(), 'files', req.params.name);
    const data = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');
    res.send(data);
  } catch (err) {
    res.status(404).send('File not found');
  }
});

app.listen(3000);
```

**Common interview trap:** Not validating file paths allows directory traversal attacks (../../../); use path.join() and validate inputs.

